properties.otherAdvice:
Kamilaroi Hwy from Walgett to Brewarrina is closed

properties.diversions:
Bourke to Walgett: Mitchell Hwy to Dubbo, Newell Hwy to Gilgandra, Castlereagh Hwy to Walgett.

Brewarrina to Bourke Arthur Hall Vc Way to Coolabah, Mitchell Hwy to Bourke.

properties.headline: FLOODING WALGETT TO BOURKE Kamilaroi Highway CLOSED
properties.otherAdvice:
The road is flooded approximately 65km west of Walgett.

Kamilaroi Hwy is also closed from Brewarrina to Bourke

Castlereagh Hwy 15km south of Walgett is closed to light vehicles
properties.diversions: From Brewarrina to Wallgett: Arthur Hall Vc Way to Coolabah, Mitchell Hwy to Dubbo, Newell Hwy to Gilgandra, Castlereagh Hwy to Walgett.

properties.otherAdvice: Other local roads in the Forbes Shire Council area may be closed due to flooding or affected by recent adverse weather. Visit the council's website for further information.

properties.headline: FLOODING FORBES TO GOOLOOGONG Lachlan Valley Way CLOSED
properties.otherAdvice: Lachlan Valley Way from Cowra to Gooloogong is open under alternating stop/slow traffic conditions.
properties.diversions:
Motorists to use Newell Hwy, Mid Western Hwy to travel between Cowra and Forbes.

This is suitable for all vehicles.

properties.headline: FLOODING COREEN Riverina Highway CLOSED between Federation Way and Bull Plain Road
properties.diversions:
Eastbound: Bull Plain Rd, Spring Dr and Federation Ave to Corowa, then Honour Ave to return to Riverina Hwy south of Lowesdale.

Westbound: Riverina Hwy and Hounour Ave to Corowa, then Spring Dr and Bull Plain Rd to return to the Riverina Hwy.

This diversion is suitable for all vehicles.

properties.otherAdvice:
Closure due to current flood evacuation advice in Echuca.

Northbound will remain open.
The Newell Highway is also closed northbound between Kidman Way and Kerrylands Road.
properties.diversions:
Jerilderie to Narrandera: Kidman Way, Whitton Rd and Irrigation Way

Narrandera to Jerilderie: Irrigation Way, Whitton Rd and Kidman Way

properties.otherAdvice: The Newell Highway is also closed in both directions between Kerrylands Road and Gillenbah (south of Narrandera)
properties.diversions: Kidman Way, Whitton Rd and Irrigation Way

properties.headline: FLOODING WILCANNIA TO IVANHOE Cobb Highway CLOSED
properties.diversions:
Southbound from Wilcannia: Barrier Hwy to Cobar, Kidman Way to Goolgowi, and Mid Western Hwy to Hay.

Northbound from Hay: Mid Western Hwy to Goolgowi, Kidman Way to Cobar, and Barrier Hwy to Wilcannia.

This route is suitable for all vehicles and will add around 4hrs to your travel time.

properties.otherAdvice:
The road remains closed to most vehicles, but can be open with extreme caution to 4WD only with 5ton limit.

Local residents will be allowed access.
properties.diversions: Heavy vehicles could use Newell Hwy from Moree to Boggabilla for access into QLD at Goondiwindi.

properties.headline: FLOODING DARLINGTON POINT TO COLLINGULLIE Sturt Highway between Kidman Way and Lockhart Road
properties.diversions:
Westbound from Wagga Wagga: Coolamon Rd, Canola Way and Newell Hwy to Narrandera, then Irrigation Way, Whitton Darlington Point Rd and Kidman Way - Suitable for heavy vehicles up to 25/26m B-Double only

Eastbound from Darlington Point: Kidman Way, Whitton Darlington Point Rd and Irrigation Way to Narrandera, then Newell Hwy, Canola Way and Coolamon Rd to Wagga Wagga - Suitable for heavy vehicles up to 25/26m B-Double only

(Also for people wanting to reach VIC).

properties.otherAdvice: The road is closed to all vehicles.
properties.diversions:
Eastbound: Oxley Hwy to Nevertire, Mitchell Hwy to Dubbo, Newell Hwy to Gilgandra.

Westbound: Newell Hwy to Dubbo, Mitchell Highway to Nevertire to the Oxley Highway.

properties.headline: FLOODING NARRABRI TO BOGGABILLA Newell Highway CLOSED
properties.otherAdvice: The Newell Hwy is closed at a number of locations due to flooding.
properties.diversions:
From Coonabarabran: Oxley Hwy to Tamworth then join the New England Hwy to Queensland.


Alternatively, motorists can use the Castlereagh Hwy to travel between Gilgandra and the Queensland border via Lightning Ridge.
